    <author>Author</author>
    <guid>https://l-lin.github.io/2018-08-31-postgresql_remove_idle_transactions/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="https://www.virtual-dba.com/media/postgresql-database-services-remote-dba.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span><span class="lnt">2
</span><span class="lnt">3
</span><span class="lnt">4
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre class="chroma"><code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"><span class="k">SELECT</span> <span class="n">pg_terminate_backend</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pid</span><span class="p">)</span> 
<span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="n">pg_stat_activity</span> 
<span class="k">WHERE</span> <span class="k">state</span> <span class="k">LIKE</span> <span class="s1">&#39;idle %&#39;</span> 
<span class="k">AND</span> <span class="n">state_change</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">now</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="nb">interval</span> <span class="s1">&#39;1 hour&#39;</span><span class="p">;</span>
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div>]]></description>
</item><item>
    <title>How to link old and new IDs when migrating data from one table to another</title>
    <link>https://l-lin.github.io/2018-03-29-postgresql_insert_and_link_ids/</link>
    <pubDate>Thu, 29 Mar 2018 11:25:34 &#43;0200</pubDate>
    <author>Author</author>
    <guid>https://l-lin.github.io/2018-03-29-postgresql_insert_and_link_ids/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="https://www.virtual-dba.com/media/postgresql-database-services-remote-dba.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><p>When proceeding a database migration, I often had to create a temporary table that will contains
the data from the old database.</p>
<p>However, after the migration, I still need to have links between the old IDs and the new IDs for
various post migration operation.</p>
<p>This post is about creating the table containing the linked ids.</p>]]></description>
